\v 30 There are \add also\add* the princes of \add the\add* north, all of them, all of \add the\add* Sidonians who have gone down, being ashamed \add to lie\add* with \add the\add* slain because\f + \fr 32:30 \ft Or “in spite of” (cf. NJPS, NIV) \f* of their terror \add that they caused\add* from their might, and they lie uncircumcised with \add those killed\add* by \add the\add* sword, and they bear their disgrace \add along with\add* \add the people\add* going down to \add the\add* grave.\f + \fr 32:30 \ft Or “pit” \f*
